commitResults.messageTitle: Added Greet, Echo, Exit to Duke

commitResults.messageBody:
Break down one larger input command into multiple smaller inputs from the user.

The previous versions of Duke accepted one single input to be parsed into multiple different commands.
This led to certain difficulties in parsing those commands.

Breaking down one singular Input command into multiple smaller input mitigates risks of incorrect parsing
of commands.

At each stage of requesting the user for input, the format of the input is explicitly stated to minimize cases of
invalid input fomats. On top of that, each input from the user should also be checked for validity.

Higher levels of interaction between Duke and user can allow users to feel more involved when using Duke,
in order to improve overall user experience.

Null checks should not exist! Replaced null checks with EmptyTask check.

In order to make more use of OOP, task related methods have been delegated to the TaskManager class.
Date manager allows for greater flexibility for printing of dates in different formats.
TaskCreator handles creation of task when loading up saved data and also when tasks are created during normal task addition.
Issues included: Unused imports, Wrong task constructors used

TimeManager.java allows Duke to properly process time from a 24-hr format into both the 24-hr and 12-hr formats.
Minor changes were made to allow duke to better process and store date and time.

commitResults.messageTitle: Bugfix after the merging of level 7 and level 8
commitResults.messageBody: Minor incompatibility issues arouse after merging level 7 and level 8. This version of Duke tackles those issues.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor to better make use of OOP
commitResults.messageBody: Further separation of codes into their different components allow for smoother troubleshooting process

commitResults.messageTitle: Add new feature  to clear list.
commitResults.messageBody:
Clear allows user to instantly clear the tasklist.
Fixed bugs relating to date and time
Code was tweaked to comply with given coding standard also.
Duke can now be run using Gradle
Checkstyle is now supported on Gradle
Prepping for javafx here. (No javafx codes added yet)
The addition of a GUI to Duke greatly improve user experience!

The naming conventions of the various command classes and task classes seem uneccessarily confusing. Let's
change the names of these ckasses. E.g. CommandDeadline -> DeadlineCommand

It seems that the '-' infront of the JavaDocs method parameter comments have been
repeated. Let's remove those uneccessary regexes and clean up all JavaDocs as well.
The dialog box is not showing all the text in it. Let's fix it.
Duke shows the feature list at start up and it fills up the whole screen. The feature list belongs on the user manual so let's remove that.

The previous GUI displays all messages in the same color. Let's make the GUI reflect invalid inputs from the user by making those messages a different color.

Images on Duke and user have also been changed in this version.
Fixed issue where unmarking of tasks could not be completed as well.
